==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aguish
<hw>A"gu*ish</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having
the qualities of an ague; somewhat cold or shivering; chilly;
shaky.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her <qex>aguish</qex> love now glows and burns.</q>
<rj><qau>Granville.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Productive of, or affected by, ague; <as>as, the
<ex>aguish</ex> districts of England</as>.</def> <rj><au>T.
Arnold.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>A"gu*ish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Agush</ent>⟦br⟧
